## Practical Realities

- Despite the complexity, software engineering allows people to build powerful programs without deep understanding of underlying hardware.
- Debugging often starts with doing nothing and rerunning code before more complex investigation.
- Managing printers and other peripherals remains a practical skill for programmers, reinforcing the importance of understanding hardware interaction.

