### Summary & Key Takeaways
- Computers operate on bits and bytes, controlled by CPUs and memory, abstracted by operating systems and programming languages.
- Programming languages convert human-friendly code into machine code, with varied typing and execution models.
- Data structures and algorithms are essential tools for organizing and processing data efficiently.
- Understanding paradigms (declarative, imperative, OOP) helps write clearer, reusable, and scalable code.
- Modern computing relies on virtualization, networking protocols, and secure communication to power the internet.
- Practical software engineering balances deep technical knowledge with abstractions that make coding accessible and productive.
- Algorithms must be evaluated on efficiency using Big-O notation to ensure scalability.
- Concurrency and parallelism improve program performance on modern multi-core CPUs.
- Mastery of these concepts enables building reliable, efficient, and secure software systems.
